															<div class="description">
									<p data-start="511" data-end="742"><strong data-start="511" data-end="520">Depik</strong> is a peer-reviewed open-access journal published by Universitas Syiah Kuala, Indonesia. The journal is accredited by the Ministry of Education, Culture, Research, and Technology of the Republic of Indonesia (<strong data-start="729" data-end="740">SINTA 2</strong>).</p>
<p data-start="744" data-end="1004">Depik publishes original research articles in the fields of aquatic and fisheries sciences, including fisheries (aquaculture, capture fisheries, and fish processing), aquatic ecology (freshwater, marine, and brackish water), aquatic biology, and oceanography.</p>
<p data-start="1006" data-end="1305">The journal is jointly published by the Faculty of Marine and Fisheries, Universitas Syiah Kuala, in collaboration with the Indonesian Association of Oceanologists (Aceh Chapter), Graduate School of Universitas Syiah Kuala, and the Center for Marine and Fisheries Studies of Universitas Syiah Kuala.</p>
<p data-start="1307" data-end="1458">Depik is published <strong data-start="1326" data-end="1351">three issues per year (2012 to 2024)</strong>, <strong>four issues per year (Starting on 2025),</strong><strong> </strong>and applies a rigorous peer-review process to ensure the quality and originality of published manuscripts.</p>
