															<div class="description">
									<p data-start="188" data-end="580"><strong data-start="188" data-end="214">Sport Pedagogy Journal</strong> is a peer-reviewed, open-access academic journal dedicated to the development and dissemination of knowledge in the fields of <strong data-start="341" data-end="412">sport pedagogy, physical education, and sport teaching and learning</strong>. The journal serves as a scholarly platform for researchers, lecturers, teachers, practitioners, and policy makers to publish high-quality and impactful academic work.</p>
<p data-start="582" data-end="883">The journal applies a <strong data-start="604" data-end="631">full open-access policy</strong>, allowing all published articles to be freely accessed and downloaded without subscription fees. This policy aims to broaden the dissemination of scientific knowledge and to promote the wide exchange of ideas at both national and international levels.</p>
<p data-start="885" data-end="1340">The focus and scope of <strong data-start="908" data-end="934">Sport Pedagogy Journal</strong> include, but are not limited to: sport pedagogy, physical and health education, sport teaching and learning methods and strategies, curriculum development, learning assessment, professional development of sport and physical education teachers and lecturers, inclusive and adaptive physical education, coaching pedagogy, technology-enhanced sport learning, as well as sport education policy and management.</p>
<p data-start="1342" data-end="1608">All submitted manuscripts undergo a rigorous and transparent <strong data-start="1403" data-end="1426">peer-review process</strong> to ensure academic quality, originality, and relevance. The journal upholds the highest standards of <strong data-start="1528" data-end="1550">publication ethics</strong>, academic integrity, and responsible scholarly practices.</p>
<p data-start="1610" data-end="1901">Copyright of the published articles remains with the authors, while the journal is granted the right of first publication. Articles are published under a <strong data-start="1764" data-end="1792">Creative Commons license</strong>, allowing the use and distribution of scholarly work with proper attribution to the authors and the journal.</p>
<p data-start="1903" data-end="2157"><strong data-start="1903" data-end="1929">Sport Pedagogy Journal</strong> is committed to protecting the privacy and confidentiality of authors, reviewers, and readers. Personal data collected by the journal are used solely for journal management purposes and will not be misused for other objectives.</p>
<p data-start="2159" data-end="2346">To ensure long-term preservation and accessibility of its digital content, the journal supports electronic archiving systems as part of its commitment to sustainable scholarly publishing.</p>
