<p data-start="0" data-end="664"><strong>JPED: Jurnal Perspektif Ekonomi Darussalam (Darussalam Journal of Economic Perspectives) </strong>is a scientific journal established as a platform for publishing research findings, conceptual studies, and academic ideas in the fields of economics, management, business, and development. The journal is committed to supporting the advancement of knowledge through the publication of high-quality, innovative, and relevant scientific works that address local, national, and global economic dynamics. By upholding strong academic standards, JPED serves as a scholarly medium that encourages the exchange of ideas among academics, researchers, practitioners, and students.</p>
<p data-start="666" data-end="1216">As an academic journal, JPED provides space for various perspectives in economic studies, including Islamic economics, development economics, entrepreneurship, finance, public policy, and contemporary socio-economic issues. Every article published undergoes a peer-review process to ensure quality, objectivity, and scientific integrity. The presence of this journal is expected to make a meaningful contribution to the development of research and the strengthening of academic literacy within higher education institutions and the broader community.</p>
<p data-start="1218" data-end="1764" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">JPED also strives to build broader academic networks through collaboration among researchers and educational institutions at both national and international levels. With a spirit of openness in knowledge dissemination, the journal encourages the publication of research capable of offering solutions to various economic and development challenges in the modern era. Through continuous publication, JPED is expected to become a credible and competitive scientific reference in the advancement of economics and sustainable development perspectives.</p>
