<p data-start="0" data-end="545"><strong><span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">Jurnal Ilmiah Mahasiswa Ekonomi Islam (JIMEKI)</span></span></strong> is an academic publication medium that focuses on the development of knowledge in the field of Islamic economics. This journal publishes various scientific works such as research articles, theoretical studies, and academic ideas related to the principles of Islamic economics. The existence of this journal serves as an important platform in supporting the development of high-quality scientific literature that is relevant to the needs of society and the advancement of Islamic economics in the modern era.</p>
<p data-start="547" data-end="1025">This journal also functions as a platform for students, researchers, lecturers, and academics to publish their research findings. Through these publications, authors can share ideas, research discoveries, and solutions to various economic issues occurring in society. In addition, scientific publication in the journal can enhance the culture of writing, critical thinking, and academic skill development, especially for students who are learning to conduct scientific research.</p>
<p data-start="1027" data-end="1467" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">The topics published in this journal cover various fields related to Islamic economics, such as Sharia economics, Islamic banking, Islamic finance, Islamic business, zakat, waqf, and Sharia-based business management. With such a broad scope of themes, this journal is expected to become a valuable scientific reference source for readers, researchers, and practitioners in understanding and developing Islamic economic concepts more deeply.</p>
